    <h2>Your 90-day longevity<br>lab plan</h2>

    <p>Testing is only useful if it leads to action. Here's a practical 90-day framework — from baseline to optimized — built around the 10 markers in this guide.</p>

    <div class="guide-plan">

      <div class="guide-plan-phase">
        <div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-label">Phase 1</div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-week">Week 1</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Establish your baseline</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Order all 10 markers — either à la carte via Ulta or through a full panel like Superpower</li>
            <li>Fast for 10–12 hours before the draw (required for fasting insulin, triglycerides, and glucose accuracy)</li>
            <li>Draw in the morning — cortisol and testosterone follow a diurnal rhythm; morning draws are most standardized</li>
            <li>Upload your results to the <a href="/analyze" style="color:var(--green);text-decoration:none;">AgelessLabs AI analyzer</a> for a full longevity score and per-marker breakdown</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-plan-phase">
        <div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-label">Phase 2</div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-week">Weeks 2–4</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Interpret and prioritize</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Identify your 2–3 highest-leverage intervention targets — the markers furthest from optimal with the most modifiable drivers</li>
            <li>Review the full biomarker page for each target marker — understanding what moves it is as important as knowing the number</li>
            <li>Consider the Full Longevity Report ($19) for age- and sex-adjusted ranges, interaction patterns, and a prioritized protocol built from your specific results</li>
            <li>Note any markers that warrant a physician conversation — particularly Lp(a) elevation or IGF-1 outside the optimal zone</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-plan-phase">
        <div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-label">Phase 3</div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-week">Weeks 4–12</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h4>Implement and track</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Implement targeted interventions for your 2–3 priority markers — diet, supplementation, sleep, exercise, or medication as appropriate</li>
            <li>Most markers respond meaningfully within 8–12 weeks of consistent intervention — HbA1c, hsCRP, fasting insulin, and Omega-3 Index all have predictable response timelines</li>
            <li>ApoB and Lp(a) may require pharmacological support if lifestyle optimization is insufficient — these are worth a frank conversation with a physician</li>
            <li>Track any relevant lifestyle variables alongside your labs — sleep, diet patterns, exercise load — to identify what's actually moving the needle</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="guide-plan-phase">
        <div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-label">Phase 4</div>
          <div class="guide-plan-phase-week">Week 12</div>
        </div>
